structured.title: Shepard Helps Expose Novaria Corruption
structured.overview: On the corporate world of Novaria, Commander Shepard navigates local corruption to gain access to Peak 15. Annelias, an internal affairs investigator, explains that executive administrator Anoleis is corrupt but too careful to keep obvious records, making Keen's testimony and financial data critical to proving his guilt. Shepard brokers a deal: Keen agrees to testify in exchange for the safe return of his property and some consideration of his interests, despite his distrust of public spectacle and law enforcement. Once Keen commits, Annelias is relieved, takes custody of the evidence, and fulfills her side of the bargain by securing Shepard a garage pass to reach Peak 15. Security then arrests Anoleis, who angrily protests and threatens Annelias's career as he is taken into custody, while another contact quietly suggests Shepard may have had a hand in his downfall. With the pass verified, Shepard heads to the garage, where a geth ambush confirms that Matriarch Benezia likely smuggled hostile synthetics in concealed shipping containers. Local security, alarmed about investor panic and their lack of combat experience, accepts Shepard's offer to handle the geth threat and proceed toward the storm-ravaged Peak 15 facility.
